cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: The paper deals with a machine learning problem (Apprenticeship Learning) and uses optimization techniques (Frank-Wolfe algorithm) to solve it. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves decision-making in a Markov Decision Process (MDP), which suggests the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The use of convex optimization techniques points towards cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
